    <item>
      <title>Join the Hunt NYC at the Content Authenticity Summit 2025</title>
      <link>https://guardianproject.github.io/info/2025/06/02/join-the-hunt-nyc-at-the-content-authenticity-summit-2025/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 02 Jun 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://guardianproject.github.io/info/2025/06/02/join-the-hunt-nyc-at-the-content-authenticity-summit-2025/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Reposted from &lt;a href=&#34;https://proofmode.org/blog/thehuntnyc&#34;&gt;proofmode.org&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Join the fun to defend reality against fakes by playing &amp;ldquo;The Hunt NYC&amp;rdquo;, a multi-day photo and video scavenger hunt held around the Content Authenticity Summit in New York City, on June 4th, 2025.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Empowering Mobile Journalism with CuttingRoom and C2PA</title>
      <link>https://guardianproject.github.io/info/2025/04/02/empowering-mobile-journalism-with-cuttingroom-and-c2pa/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 02 Apr 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://guardianproject.github.io/info/2025/04/02/empowering-mobile-journalism-with-cuttingroom-and-c2pa/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Reposted from &lt;a href=&#34;https://proofmode.org/blog/cuttingroom&#34;&gt;proofmode.org&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CuttingRoom and ProofMode Team Up for Content Authenticity Support on iPhones&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;In today&amp;rsquo;s digital landscape, where increasingly &amp;ldquo;AI Slop&amp;rdquo; runs rampant, the integrity of media has never been more critical. It&amp;rsquo;s a constant battle to discern fact from fiction, and the stakes are high. That&amp;rsquo;s why we&amp;rsquo;re thrilled to announce a partnership that aims to arm journalists and content creators with a powerful weapon in this fight: the integration of the Coalition for Content Provenance and Authentication (C2PA) standard into the CuttingRoom Reporter mobile app for iOS.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Generative AI Detection in ProofCheck</title>
      <link>https://guardianproject.github.io/info/2025/03/18/generative-ai-detection-in-proofcheck/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 18 Mar 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://guardianproject.github.io/info/2025/03/18/generative-ai-detection-in-proofcheck/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Reposted from &lt;a href=&#34;https://proofmode.org/blog/proofcheckai&#34;&gt;proofmode.org&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;ProofCheck is our free and open-source, multi-purpose &amp;ldquo;Swiss Army Knife&amp;rdquo; tool for image, video, and audio metadata inspection. It can work with the &amp;ldquo;Proof Pack&amp;rdquo; bundle zip files that are produced by our ProofMode camera app, and it can also inspect any multimedia file you try to throw at it. It will look for metadata formats like EXIF, C2PA, IPTC, and more, and validate ProofMode PGP signatures, OpenTimestamp notarization, and other cryptographic signatures. All of this happens locally in your browser, without any uploads to a server, ensuring privacy of your media and metadata is maintained.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
